Can you provide information on the charge, monoisotopic weight and hydrogen bond donors of a chemical species with an atom chiral undef count greater than 0.9? It must fall under Nitrogen Compounds class and be utilized as Fuel.

query.sparql:
SELECT ?Charge ?MonoIsotopicWeight ?HydrogenBondDonorCount WHERE {
  ?Species os:hasAtomChiralUndefCount/os:value ?AtomChiralUndefCountValue .
  FILTER ( ?AtomChiralUndefCountValue > 0.9 )
  ?Species os:hasChemicalClass/rdfs:label "Nitrogen Compounds" .
  ?Species os:hasUse/rdfs:label "Fuel" .
  ?Species os:hasCharge ?Charge .
  ?Species os:hasMonoIsotopicWeight ?MonoIsotopicWeight .

}
